      <p class="signal-section-intro">The job search is full of silence. At the same time, you generate real work signals every time you open up your coding client. Signal is built to increase your leverage in any job search, starting with the work you've already done.</p>

      <div class="signal-problem-solution">
        <div class="signal-ps-item">
          <p class="signal-ps-problem">Your resume doesn't show what you've actually built.</p>
          <p class="signal-ps-solution">Resumes are summaries written under pressure, optimized for keywords. They flatten your real work into bullet points that rarely capture what you actually shipped, debugged, or figured out. Signal starts somewhere different.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="signal-ps-item">
          <p class="signal-ps-problem">Your sessions become your profile.</p>
          <p class="signal-ps-solution">Every time you've worked through a problem in Claude Code, Cursor, or Codex — that's real evidence. Signal processes those sessions and extracts what actually happened: the technologies you used, the problems you solved, the architectural decisions you made. No form to fill out. The work is already there.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="signal-ps-item">
          <p class="signal-ps-problem">Know where you fit, honestly.</p>
          <p class="signal-ps-solution">Paste a job description. Signal scores your fit across Skills, Alignment, and Personality — grounded in your actual history, not your resume claims. An honest read in five minutes is worth more than three rounds of interviews that go nowhere.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="signal-ps-item">
          <p class="signal-ps-problem">It works both ways.</p>
          <p class="signal-ps-solution">Share your Signal with recruiters or engineering leads. They have a real conversation with it and walk away with a live fit score — without a resume ever changing hands.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

